  "informal_statement": "For every real x ≥ 2, ∫_2^x (log t + 1) · 2√t · log t/(t² log² t) dt ≤ 2√2 · (1 + 1/log 2).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Cancel one log factor, dominate the remaining integrand by a constant multiple of t^(−3/2)-type decay, and integrate the dominating kernel explicitly on [2, ∞).",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem mertens_error_integral_sqrt_bound :\n    ∀ x : ℝ, 2 ≤ x →\n      (∫ t in (2:ℝ)..x, (Real.log t + 1) * (2 * Real.sqrt t * Real.log t) / (t^2 * (Real.log t)^2))\n        ≤ 2 * Real.sqrt 2 * (1 + (Real.log 2)⁻¹)",
